## Proposed Folder Structure

We will create a multi-package workspace with a root-level orchestrator. Running a single command (`npm run dev`) at the root will launch both the Express backend and the Next.js frontend simultaneously!

```
ShipSync/
├── package.json               # Root orchestrator (scripts to run frontend & backend concurrently)
├── backend/                   # Node.js + Express.js API Server
│   ├── package.json
│   ├── .env.example
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── index.js           # Server Entrypoint
│   │   ├── controllers/       # Auth, OCR, Excel, Billing, Dashboard controllers
│   │   ├── routes/            # Express router setups
│   │   ├── services/          # OCR Service, Excel Service, Fuzzy Matching Service
│   │   ├── middleware/        # Auth middleware, File upload (Multer)
│   │   └── utils/             # Math and Helper functions
│   └── prisma/
│       ├── schema.prisma      # Prisma schema file (configured for SQLite, easily switchable to Postgres)
│       └── dev.db             # Local SQLite database
├── frontend/                  # Next.js React Web App
│   ├── package.json
│   ├── tailwind.config.js     # Premium theme customizations (glassmorphism, dark/light colors)
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── app/               # Next.js App Router (Layouts, Pages, Dashboard)
│   │   ├── components/        # Elegant UI Components (Card, Charts, FileUploader, Table)
│   │   ├── styles/            # CSS, Animations, custom tailwind styles
│   │   └── utils/             # API clients, local storage helpers
```

